{
  "texts": [
    "One possibility is that the model simply adapts by learning this new factual information.",
    "However, a common conjecture posits that such exposure to new knowledge may encourage the model to hallucinate factually incorrect responses, as the model is essentially trained to generate facts that are not grounded in its pre-existing knowledge (Schulman, 2023; Huang et al., 2023; Gao, 2021; Goldberg, 2023; Gudibande et al., 2023).",
    "In this work, we study how learning new factual arXiv:2405.05904v3 [cs.CL] 1 Oct 2024 knowledge through fine-tuning impacts the model's tendency to hallucinate w.r.t.",
    "its pre-existing knowledge, exploring the above conjecture.",
    "1 To study the impact of new knowledge, we must be able to assess whether a single fine-tuning example is consistent with the model's knowledge."
  ]
}